caption: Terrible. Smelled like trash outside and inside. And the food literally tasted like and smelled like trash. I couldn't finish it. Waste of money. I dont understand the reviews at all. At all. These reviews are now mad sus. My experience and the reviews do not add up at all. Im disturbed by this.
Not too shabby!! The man working counter was very helpful and engaging--and tacos were delicious if not a lil pricey. It's in a basement setting, so don't expect anything super fancy.
Absolute best tacos in dc.
I LOVE the Tacos..... I have literally tried all of them. Great spot to grab and go. Specially at late hours......
This place is soooo good. The duck taco is amazing!

Delicious!!! We highly recommend the chicken and the chickpea tacos. Great gluten corn tortilla option available as well. Really friendly service too. Located just off the Metro stop in Dupont. Will be going back again and again :)
The staff is always courteous and patient...food is yummy yum yum!

Tiki Taco keeps the aloha spirit alive in DC! The food is always so fresh and delicious and the guys working their are so friendly! The coconut shrimp taco is insanely good. Go support this awesome local business!
I love this place , clean , fast and so good Loco moco.
When I’m sad I come get my Tiki fix and dream of a Hawaiian breeze. The new fried chicken taco is incredible!
Beat tacos, softshell, coconut shrimp and pork belly
the food is always great, along with the service.
Best tacos for cheap in the DC area. Give it a shot if you’re near DuPont

Went there on Sunday the guy working behind the register who was also going back and forth in the kitchen did not have masks on properly mask was below his nose he had terrible attitude when asked to pull his mask up would not eat there again and would not suggest anyone else goals if you care about not catching Covid

Food is average. Poke is a cold dish. When you put it with super hot rice on the same to go container it will cook the fish. The tiki poke was tasteless. Cooks were not wearing masks. Guy who took my order was doing the below the nose thing with his mask. Come on people!!
Best coconut shrimp tacos I’ve ever had!!!
Delicious tacos. Love the selection.
The Kalua pork plate lunch was very good.

NEVER disappoints! My favorite quick meal in the city. Cheap, fast, unique, and tasty! The fact that you have to take stairs under another shop makes it feel like you've discovered a new hole-in-the-wall place to show off to your friends.
Fantastic!
All  takos  is  the best  in dc...✌✌😄😄
Wow, these were legit some of the best tacos I've ever had.
Perfect food to get after a long day of travel!
Soooo goooood! I've been here twice and both times the tacos were great. Highly recommend the coconut shrimp! Delicious.
Spicy Pineapple Wings. 8 pieces, lots of měst for a very good price. Tasty poke bowls.
Awesome island fare.  Food is excellent!
The best tacos around!
Malasadas!!!!  And they were good malasadas!!! (And the service was fantastic)

Super fast, fresh, delicious poke. The Tina was big and chunky and the spices on top were amazing. Didn't get the tacos, but definitely would try! Super fast, in and out in 20. A little small so be prepared.
Great place, full of diverse Taco's
One of the few places I've gone out of my way to recommend to friends.  Unique concept in DC.  Service has been top notch too.

I had the Kailua pork and pork belly tacos. Pork belly had a real nice char to it. The Kailua pork is kind of like a pulled pork but with a sweetness you don't generally get from Midwestern pulled pork. Homemade salsa was legit. Not hot at all with a good flavor.
I walked past this place countless times. It's in the basement. Can't believe I missed out on the tacos. Rotating menu keeps it fresh.
Fresh & good!!
Great food and great service. A must visit place !
Great three pack of tacos served very quickly!
Delicious tacos! My husband and son tried half the menu. Everything was flavorful. Highly recommend.
Philly Cheesesteak Taco is the best... I hope it becomes permanent on the menu
What a find! Amazing flavors...and so many to choose from.
YUM! Affordable, too.
Absolutely great flavors and service! Couldn't recommend high enough.
Great vegetarian options
Friendly staff 👍Mickey👍Delicious food at a reasonable price. The Key Lime Pie is Wonderful.

This place is fantastic. The atmosphere is low key and the staff are friendly. Most important the tacos are delicious! The salsas and garnishes on the tacos are unique and very fresh. Presentation is good too. For planning purposes note that they do not have a bathroom nor do they serve alcohol. Oh and they have rotating specials. I tried a mushroom taco from the specials and it was delicious! Can't wait to go again.
Great tacos that filled me to my core.  Excellent atmosphere too.  Will return again.
Wow is all I can say. I will be back for sure.
AMAZING!!! Inexpensive and incredible tasting tacos. I cannot recommend this place enough. Quick service and very chill. If you’re looking for tasty and creative tacos give this place a visit.
Soooo good. I got the traditional ahi poke, it’s not cheap but you get a huge portion of ahi, and the seasoning and sauce are tasty!
Amazing tacos and poke.  Would 100 percent go back.
Tacos were delish but skip the shave ice unless you need to dye your tongue.

The food there is super great, and the staff is really nice. The quality of foodstuff within each and every meal is so good. The taco meat is actually warm, and so flavorful. Would definitely recommend!
Had the taco salad it was amazingly fresh and vibrant.

A cute tiny restaurant filled with flavor! On the walls you will see pictures of Hawaii, the decor is tasteful and the staff are helpful. We ordered the Island (Alaskan Cod), Jerk Chicken and Beef Tacos. Along with those we also ordered the Spicy Pineapple Wings. Everything was filled with so much flavor! If you’re like me and need extra spiciness to your food, use their house-made hot sauce- perfect!
This place is fire

Small place that seemed to have constant traffic for the shave ice. The guy that rang us up was friendly and helpful (he knew immediately we were out-of-towners). The tacos were great, my wife said the poke was very good. I had the key lime pie for dessert and all I can do is make the Homer Simpson drooling sound, it was the perfect balance of tart and sweet. My kids got some shave ice and they were both very flavorful.
Beat shaved ice
Small little hidden gem. The staff was awesome. Super friendly! The food was amazing. The chips and guacamole was the best I've ever had. Don't pass this tiny little place by!

I had a classic beef, pork belly and chicken taco. Three tacos for $10.50. It was delish. The thing that I like about this place is the tacos don't make you feel like you just got ripped off. These are not tiny tacos and they are packed with ingredients. Made me wish that I lived in DC. It's a walk downstairs to enter Tiki Taco. The inside is very small so I imagine that there are days that the seating might be a challenge. Otherwise these are top 5 tacos that I've had in the United States.

My experience was great, the island music made it a relaxed environment. The cashier helped me with my selection and I must say I'm glad I asked.. The chili pepper sauce should be placed in different bottles because it kept clogging up. The food is made to order so expect a little wait depending on what you ordered. Customer service was A+. I totally recommend it to those who would like a cheap filling eat on the go. I'm looking forward to returning. Good job guys 👏💪💪👏
The best food in DC. Even greater staff
I can't express anything but love for this place, great service, and the best tacos.

Had this place delivered. Managed to deliver the blandest version of one of the easiest foods to make. The tacos were completely flavorless and the poke was questionably without citrus. Will never eat from here again.

Tiki Taco is an underground destination for Hawaii-inspired tacos, salads, and poke bowls. The pork, beef, and fish tacos have a good, complex flavor. A worthy stop ahead of a night out. No beer, wine, or alcohol but some soft drinks from the islands.
Great tacos!!!
My husband and I both had delicious poke bowls. So fresh and tasty!
Some of the best flavor in tacos I have had in a long while.  The staff are super nice and eager to assist.  We topped off the meal with a classic shaved ice!
Amazing tacos. Great late night spot

Stopped by this shop randomly. Decided to go for the tacos and my fianceé did the salmon poke. The jerk chicken, coconut shrimp and the beef taco all tasted amazing. The gentleman who took our order/served our food was extremely nice and helpful during my first experience with this place. It's a small spot so it won't be the best for huge groups (12+) but it's definitely worth a visit.

Awful experience with your pokes. You guys dropped a pack of salt in there. When calling to let you know of our experience you just said "thanks for letting us know" without offering any change in our dinner. How can you have 5 stars, seriously.
Pokeball made with salt salt salt salt salt and salt again. Made to hide the bad taste. Impossible to eat. Poor quality and quantity. Will never order again
Staff was very friendly, had many flavors to choose from. I loved my snow ball, the ice was so soft and fluffy. Absolutely love this place.
Great food and nice people!
I have passed this place often, never visiting. Today was the best day of my lunch life! The jerk chicken taco is killer superb! I shall return tomorrow. Great service too.
Great tacos (especially the pork-belly taco). Can't wait to try again.
If you go there aren't any restrooms. Service was average, food was average and way over priced
This place was AMAZING! The tacos were very fresh and each one was delicious! My husband and I are pretty picky foodies and we both thought it was top notch! Highly recommend...
Love love love this place! Shrimp tacos are my favorite. Try the shaved ice every flavor counts 👏🏾👏🏾😜😜🤓😁😁

So good I had to leave a review, great flavors and very filling! I got the tofu, beef and jerk chicken options (wanted to mix it up)... For some reason I went there expecting a Latina influence, although the name doesnt imply that lol! Anyway, I was pleasantly surprised at the flavor combinations - definitely a Pacific islander influence, so be aware of that! The photo I took isnt the most appealing but I thought I'd share anyway!

Awesome tacos. I tried the duck, jerk chicken and fish tacos on corn tortillas. Also tried the classic beef, which was just your basic classic beef. This fish was as good as most. The duck and jerk chicken are must haves.
Great price and delicious tacos.
Great flavours and unusual (but tasty) combinations. Well worth the visit
Best tacos I have had in a long time
Their tacos are so delicious!!
This is Hawaiian food at its best. If this place is busy, wait for a seat, it is worth it. If you haven't ate all day, get the Loco Moco. It will fill you up.
I went there today and the Tacos were really good. Believe this coming ; coming from a Nigerian. I was saucy and lovely
Great service and really tasty tacos.

We went in looking for Mexican food, but the place is a mix of Jamaican food with basic Mexican food. And they didn't even have good choices on the menu. When we walked in there, the smell in there was intolerable. We couldn't even stay there more than a few minutes and we left.
Excellent! Very tasty Recommended: Ahi (tuna) shoyu Poke, coconut shrimp taco, pork belly taco

Hands down my go to place for interesting, tasty and authentic tacos. Great location in DuPont and awesome visibility from the street... yellow and red signs! Love how the owner lived 6 years in Hawaii and when he had to return to the dc / nova area he decided to bring Hawaian tacos and shaved ice To dc... thank you!! The chips are to die for! It's like a mix of of corn flour and pita chips. I honestly ate the entire bowl. Queso was pipping hot and truly queso. Not floury like chipotles and not fake like Tostitos. The CHICKEN WINGS. We got the blue cheese wings. So so good. I think I'd come to tiki just for the wings. Meat fell off the bone. For tacos we got the Kailua pork, jerk chicken and fish. The pork also fell apart in my mouth and I loved the spicy mayo drizzle on the fish ones. Can't forget about the poke! It tasted super fresh and the mango pieces added a super nice fruity taste that complemented the savory dish. Last but not least we had the shaved ice! So colorful and bursting with flavor! Can't wait to return. Awesome location for a quick lunch... forget about chipotle tiki Taco is where it's at!

Great place with a lot of options that you can rarely go wrong with -- but take it from me: you want those shrimp tacos folks. Also peach shaved ice with condensed milk: a match made in heaven for the summertime. We love it
Great, great place! Service is amazing, food is outstanding, music is perfect. Highly recommend!
Best Tacos Ever!

You’re welcome in advance for telling you about one of the yummiest places in Dupont.  Located on 2010 P Street NW, Tiki Taco is one of those hole-in-the-wall that make all your dreams come true.  Their food’s super fresh, super affordable, and super effing delicious.  They specialize in three menu items:  tacos, pokes, and wings.  If you like sashimi, their shoyu ahi poke ($12) is a must-try.  It was prepared with Maui sweet onions, scallions, soy sauce, and sesame, and it was exquisite.  Also make sure to get an order of their wings - they're cheap and super flavorful! I tried them in Jerky Blue, and it's heaven for blue cheese lovers.  Their spiced pineapple flavor sounds dope though.  And last but not least, their tacos - these were everything and then some.  My favorite was their Crispy Sesame Tofu (with green papaya salad, toasted coconut, and sweet chili sauce), but their Kalbi Beef (with sesame watercress namul and hoisin crema) was also delicious.  Pro tip:  save room for dessert because they have shaved ice here with pretty much every flavor imaginable, lol.  Happy eating, friends!
Friendly staff. I love the shaved ice. Very colorful with a gummy worm on top.
Okay
Small but quaint hole in the wall. Excellent food that brings some aloha into your life.
Amazing Guac, solid tacos at a reasonable price, and good atmosphere!
Great tacos

Hands down the best taco in DC!! The owner is a veteran chef of 20 years and creating new tacos, so the menu is constantly updating. Today I tried a Portuguese pastry called Manaslada (I think that's how it's spelled) OMFG!! It was so good that I ended up buying that in addition to my tacos. I have many restaurants and taco options within walking distance of my home but I take the drive to Tiki at least 2-3 times a week. Healthy good food on a budget and great staff. I can't say enough about this place...it's well earned.
Amazing tacos. Best Poke on the east coast. Can't believe how inexpensive it is.
(Translated by Google) Very rich food. However, the establishment did not have toilets.  (Original) Muy rica la comida. Sin embargo, el establecimiento no tenía aseos.

Fabulous little hidden gem. I found my new favorite taco place. There were good choices (I can recommend the coconut shrimp and the pumpkin crusted mahi tacos) and the desert donuts dipped in chocolate were fantastic. The staff was friendly. The inside has a tiki decor (makes sense). We'll definitely be back!
Awesome Tacos and great vibe!

We went here for dinner a couple weeks ago while in D.C visiting a friend. I've been meaning to review Tiki Taco ever since. It was absolutely DELICIOUS!!! Everything was spot-on and the prices are so affordable.
Great flavors , warm atmosphere , huge fan.
Best tacos ever. Highly recommend.
ALL I CAN SAY IS!!!!!WOW!!!!!!! FISH TACOS  THE BEST  I HAVE EVER HAD AND MY NEW LUNCH JOINT
Delicious tacos. Hands down best in the area.  Also, great people and great service.

I miss Pokeworks in NY so gave this place a try.  WORST POKE I HAVE HAD IN MY LIFE.  The salmon was grey-tinged, tasted fishy and they tried to cover it up with what tasted like a bottle of vinegar.  POKE IS SUPPOSED TO BE MADE WITH SUSHI GRADE FISH, WHAT IS THIS GARBAGE?  I’m upset, disgusted and hungry.  I want my $10 back (should have known not sushi grade from the price).  Tacos would have been okay but too salty.
The fish tacos are fantastic.
Nice food, would recommend
Taco salad was good.

I have to eat here at least once a week. Everyone I've taken here loves it and now they go there often too! Also, the owner Ryan is just such a chill great guy. I love the shoyu tuna poke. Actually dangit, I think I'll go get one tonight.

Wide selection of flavors for shaved ice 🍧. I got half and half Bahama Mama and Lemon Lime, perfect when it’s in the 90s and humid. Shoyu for the poke, I wish the portion size were a little larger, but otherwise tasted great. Definitely a new favorite place for late night food in DuPont!
Delicious tacos and shaved ices... will be back soon.
Tacos are so good! My fave is the Hawaiian pork belly.
Kalua Pork tacos brought me back to Maui bite after bite.   Highly recommend.

This place surprised the hell out of me.  Just to get it out of the way, I highly recommend the pulled pork with pineapple over the crispy pork belly.  The former was soft and flavorful, the latter was overcooked and hard.  On average though, all the flavors of tacos there are pretty good.  Getting shaved ice really brought me back, and the gummi worm you get on top is a nice touch for the nostalgia train.  The owner is extremely friendly.  This place is a good alternative to Surfside, as it's open pretty late (not 24/7, not that it matters to me) and is on about the same quality and price level with a far shorter line (and wait overall).
Solid hole in the wall basement spot slinging tacos, poké bowls and shaved ice. Very limited seating but friendly staff and great food.

Delicious! I got the taco trio for under ten bucks. Had pork belly, beef, and jerk chicken tacos. All were great and they were LOADED. Typically I expect tacos to be skimped on the proteins, these were hefty and filled me up good. I have no picture because I dice right in and didn't stop to clean my fingers until I was done. Pics next time!
The flavors in the food here are bright and delicious. It’s a perfect combination of light and hearty. I’ve never ordered something that I wasn’t absolutely thrilled with. What a hidden gem!
Delicious and varied delights from an interesting basement location. Highly recommended.

Coming from a person who’s from Hawaii, I can honestly say the fish is so fresh and soft! Amazaing. I’ve not had the poke with rice and I am on my way there to pickup for dinner. Staff is also super friendly and great.
I love what they've done with this former so-so pizza joint.  have never enjoyed crispy tofu this much!  The fish tacos were also amazing.  Watch out for the spice though.
Just a random pic. But the food is really good here.
They offer a fun selection of tacos and shaved ice is an awesome addition too. Hard to find more friendly service in the area as well which is refreshing.

Honestly a wonderful find! Was searching for tacos in DC for an upcoming trip and stumbled onto it. One of the best vegetarian tacos I’ve ever had, chips were light and airy, the person I was with loved there fish tacos. Staff was friendly and nice. Truly a unique place to eat!
Great little spot with a nice variety of Taco options.  The drinks are a bit pricey but the food makes up for it
Went here for takeout. Super fast service and generous portions. Had the pork, jerk chicken, and fish tacos. All were super tasty but pork my favorite. Two tacos probably enough for me in the future!
De.li.cious!  The Poke Tiki will transport your palate from Honshū to the Mar de Cortez in a bite.  So good, I had to order a second one.
Amazing little shop with superb food like poke and loco moco. Tacos are absolutely bomb too!
Amazing tacos. 150% would recommend visiting. You will not regret. Fish taco and beef taco were amazing. Really good key lime pie too.
Tacos weren't great
Good tacos, good vegan options
Flavor town explosion 💥 These are some of the best tacos we have ever had. Portion size is perfect and to top it off they have Hawaiian shaved ice!!!!

(Translated by Google) I really like this Mexican-style restaurant. The salmon poke of 10 yuan is very delicious. In terms of the taste of a Chinese who likes to try new things, I plan to come back during Washington. recommend!  (Original) 很喜欢这个墨西哥风味餐厅，10元的三文鱼poke很美味，以一个比较喜欢尝试新鲜事物的华人的口味而言，在华盛顿期间计划再来的。推荐！

Mahalo! Awesome tacos, fun atmosphere. Had the taco trio, all very fresh and flavorful. The pork taco is exceptional and really enjoyed their take on the fish taco. Looking forward to going back again soon! If you're in DC, make the stop here.
I just had the best taco of my life. Do yourself a favor and eat here!

Tiki Taco is everything you would want from an authentic poke restaurant. I have had the other poke in the area and it does not compare or is as authentic.  Ryan puts in nice large savory cubes of either fresh tuna or salmon.  It doesn't always happen but this meal truly impressed me with the well balanced flavors.  I will definitely be coming back.
A very welcome addition to the neighborhood. No shade to Chipotle-style poke places, but it’s nice to have a more authentic option in the city. The tacos are great too!
Great food. Great service. I would be a regular if I lived here.

(Translated by Google) Good music and colorful club. Creative tacos with Hawaiian filming. Very creative  (Original) Buona musica e locale colorato. Tacos creativi con la contaminazione hawaiana. Molto creativo

A Real Gem:  Went there on St. Patrick's Day for some food after going out.  Met the owner and his sister.  The food was excellent and reasonably priced. Best part was talking to both of them, you can tell he takes the quality of his food and customer service very seriously.  I live in PA but will definitely go there again when getting down to DC. I would highly recommend it.

Would have given five stars if the food had come out a tad faster and if the person who took my order took the time to listen to me instead of asking me to repeat myself three times. That said the food and portions are AWESOME. The jerk chicken on salad was amazing and the tofu taco and kalbi beef taco are sooooo good. Cant wait to come back.
Great Hawaiian style  tacos, very flavorful, top service.
Phenomenal tacos! Woke up craving this place the next day.
